## Quick commands

```bash
./scripts/request.sh GET /api/user/profile
./scripts/request.sh POST /api/endpoint '{"key": "value"}'
./scripts/request.sh GET /api/endpoint '' production   # explicit env override
./scripts/generate-postman.sh
```

## File naming

Endpoint name = leading `/` stripped, remaining `/` replaced with `-`.

Example: `/api/Reports/daily` → `api-Reports-daily-GET.json`.

## Large responses (>=15KB)

NEVER read directly. Run summary first, then filter:

```bash
node scripts/analyze.js responses/<env>/<file>.json
node scripts/slice.js \
  responses/<env>/<source>.json \
  responses/sliced/<output>.json \
  "data.filter(r => r.status === 'active')"
```

Sliced files live in `responses/sliced/` and are reusable.
